## GCC 16 Reflection Workarounds (compiler: GCC 16.0.1 20260421)

- [P1] TODO(gcc16-workaround) — codec.hpp: `template for` (P1306 expansion
  statements) / range-for over nonstatic_data_members_of() fails in
  non-consteval context (vector<info> allocation → "not a constant expression
  because it refers to operator new").  Workaround: consteval get_member<T>(i)
  + index_sequence fold.  Revert to `template for` once GCC supports it.

- [P1] TODO(gcc16-api) — codec.hpp: nonstatic_data_members_of() requires a
  second `access_context` argument.  P2996 specifies single-arg form.  Switch
  to single-arg when the API stabilises.

- [P1] TODO(gcc16-annotations) — annotations.hpp: [[=expr]] annotation structs
  are defined but the codec does not yet query annotations_of() per-member.
  Codec always serialises big-endian without length prefix.  Wire up once GCC
  stabilises annotation reflection.

## Wire Format

- [P2] TODO(bitfield-layout) — tp.hpp: tp_header bitfield struct layout is
  implementation-defined.  We always use read_tp_header()/write_tp_header() for
  the wire format; the struct is an in-memory convenience only.

